159.question: What is typical GAN architecture for each text-to-image synhesis group?
159.response: {'Answer': 'The figure and captions depict various GAN architectures for text-to-image synthesis. The typical architectures include: Conditional GAN (cGAN), Manifold interpolation matching-aware discriminator GAN (GAN-INT-CLS), Auxiliary classifier GAN (AC-GAN), text conditioned auxiliary classifier GAN (TAC-GAN), and text conditioned semantic classifier GAN (Text-SeGAN). These architectures utilize text input to condition the generation process, with some models also incorporating auxiliary classifiers or semantic relevance checks to improve the output quality and diversity.'}
159.answer:
Semantic Enhancement GANs: DC-GANs, MC-GAN
Resolution Enhancement GANs: StackGANs, AttnGAN, HDGAN
Diversity Enhancement GANs: AC-GAN, TAC-GAN etc.
Motion Enhancement GAGs: T2S, T2V, StoryGAN
